Description.Text: The location of this hotel makes it an ideal choice for all travelers.

The hotel is located on a relatively busy, but small road just five minutes from Buckingham Palace and St. James Park tube station. Within easy walking distance of the houses of Parliament, Westminster Abbey and Victoria rail and tube station.

Due to the hotel's age, the rooms vary in size, but they are medium on average.All the rooms are in very good condition, as are the bathrooms. The room's decor varies a little but generally the style is of a traditional English hotel.

he hotel has an impressive facade in red brick with decorative stonework. An nteresting feature of the hotel is that it is built around a private courtyard, which has a central fountain and attractive flower beds.

The hotel offers a good variety of restaurants, from the Mediterranean style one to the Indian Gourmet restaurant. In summer guests can enjoy eating and drinking outside in the hotel's beautiful garden.
The lobby is large and offers plentiful seating; it is pleasantly decorated and has dark wood furniture.
